ump to navigation search cemex sab de cv type public traded as bmv cemex nyse cx bvc clh pse chp industry building materials founded   years ago  headquarters monterrey mexico area served worldwide key people rogelio zambrano lozano executive chairman fernando a gonzález ceo products cement readymix concrete construction aggregates revenue us  billion  net income us  million  total assets us  billion  number of employees  website wwwcemexcom cemex sab de cv known as cemex is a mexican multinational building materials company headquartered in san pedro near monterrey mexico it manufactures and distributes cement readymix concrete and aggregates in more than  countries it is the second largest building materials company worldwide only after lafargeholcim lorenzo zambrano was the chairman and chief executive officer until his death on may   about onethird of the companys sales come from its mexico operations a quarter from its plants in the us  from spain and smaller percentages from its plants around the worldcitation needed cemex readymix truck departing jobsite after dispensing concrete for a multistorey residential project the location is villahermosa mexico cemex currently operates on four continents with  cement plants  readymixconcrete facilities  quarries  distribution centers and  marine terminals the companys world headquarters are in san pedro garza garcía a city that is part of the monterrey metropolitan area in the northeastern mexican state of nuevo león  contents  history  internationalization   recent history   cemex worldwide  subsidiaries  social responsibility  environmental record  see also  references  external links historyedit cemex was founded with the opening of cementos hidalgo in  meanwhile cementos portland monterrey began operations in  and in  the two companies merged becoming cementos mexicanos now cemex in the s cemex grew significantly when it acquired several more plants throughout mexico in  the company went public on the mexican stock exchange and that same year became the largest cement producer in mexico with the purchase of three plants from cementos guadalajara in  the company made significant progress in overseas markets doubling its exports further acquisitions of mexican cement companies were made in  and  making cemex one of the ten largest cement companies in the world in  cemex received the wharton infosys business transformation award for their creative and efficient use of information technology internationalization edit in  cemex began its push into the international landscape with the purchase of spains two largest cement companies valenciana de cementos valcem currently head of cemex spain and cementos sanson venezuelas largest cement company vencemos was acquired by cemex in  and plants were purchased the same year in the united states and in panama in  cemex acquired a cement company in the dominican republic and with the purchase of a majority stake in a colombian cement company in  cemex became the third largest cement company in the world in  the company expanded its scope to include asia and africa making major purchases in the philippines indonesia and egypt as well as costa rica the acquisition of us based southdown made cemex the largest cement company in north america and further international purchases were made in the following two years—a thai company in  and in  a puerto rican company on march   cemex completed its  billion acquisition of the londonbased rmc group which made cemex the worldwide leader in readymix concrete production and increased its exposure to european markets with the acquisition the company expected its annual cement production to increase to  million tons also they had hoped to see its annual sales grow to  billion just shy of the market leader lafarge nyse lr which had sales of  billion as none of these targets was met cemex started looking for another suitor in its ma push on october   cemex announced a us billion offer to acquire all of the outstanding shares of rinker group limited seven months later on april   the rinker board of directors approved an upgraded offer of usd  billion and on june   cemex secured the commitment from the holders of more than  of the shares to complete the acquisition recent history edit in november  an american embassy cable released via wikileaks listed cemex among mexicos monopolists with a market share of  its competitor holcim apasco was listed with a market share of  shortly after the apparent finalization of the rinker deal on  the united states department of justice brought an antitrust lawsuit against cemex blocking the acquisition after a lengthy process cemex complied with regulators by divesting selling  cement and concrete plants formerly part of itself or rinker essentially devaluing the initial deal in april  the president of venezuela hugo chávez announced the nationalization of the whole cement industry in that country in response to the belief that the industry was exporting its products in order to receive prices above those it was allowed within the country in mid the venezuelan government took over the venezuelan operations of cemex the largest venezuelan producer with around a  market share a deal on compensation was still to be reached in march  despite agreements being reached in mid with the other two major cement producers in december  an agreement was reached with cemex receiving m in compensation and benefiting from the cancellation of m in debt after having problems with the mexican peso devaluation of  including problems with derivatives cemex had to rethink its international standings to decrease debt and avoid a default in june  cemex sold its australian operations to holcim for a  billion us billion helping refinance its us billion debt which partly was due to the acquisition two years earlier of the rinker group in december  dol resolves employee back wage case with cemex  the us department of labor announced the filing of a consent judgment in a case against cemex inc and the recovery of  in overtime back wages for  current and former readymix drivers who worked in eight states cemex worldwideedit cemex united states offices in memorial city houston cemex world corporate headquarters is in monterrey mexico and its us operations headquarters is in memorial city houston texas the company operates in over  countriesterritories around the world including  angola  argentina  brazil  brunei  canada  colombia  costa rica  croatia  czech republic  dominican republic  egypt  el salvador  finland  france  germany  haiti  hungary  ireland  indonesia  israel  jamaica  latvia  malaysia  mexico  morocco  nicaragua  nigeria  norway  panama  philippines  poland  puerto rico  singapore  spain  sweden   switzerland  trinidad  turkey  united arab emirates  united kingdom  united states subsidiariesedit cemento ponce general see ponce cement inc  ponce puerto rico puerto rican cement company  guaynabo puerto rico compania valencia de cementos portland sa  madrid spain rinker materials corporation  west palm beach florida united states cemex australia pty limited  chatswood australia cemex asia holdings ltd  philippines cxnetworks  miami florida united states cemex usa  houston texas united states western rail road  new braunfels texas united states cemex uk limited  thorpe surrey united kingdom new sunward holding  amsterdam netherlands cena acquisitions corporation  houston texas united states cemex mexico  monterrey nuevo leon mexico ready mix usa birmingham alabama caribbean cement company limited  kingston jamaica trinidad cement limited  trinidad social responsibilityedit cemex has developed a number of educational and social responsibility initiatives for example it instituted the premio cemex an annual award that recognizes works in the fields of sustainability accessibility construction and architecture also it funds the catedra blanca an honors architecture courses in three universities the itesm in monterrey the universidad iberoamericana in mexico city and the barcelona school of architecture also cemex has created the centro cemextecnológico de monterrey which is a research and development program for sustainable communities across mexico thru the premio cemextec in  the organization of american states oas through their trust for the americas awarded the company the corporate citizen of the americas award  for the social benefits of their program patrimonio hoy in mexico that according to josé miguel insulza president of the oas has a positive effect in lowincome families this initiative conceived in  aims to reduce the mexican housing deficit which leaves more than  million people with inadequate shelter patrimonio hoy organizes lowincome families into selffinancing cells that facilitate and expedite the typical homebuilding process cemex and its network provide the products needed but also the technical assistance including an architect who helps design homes to optimize space and reduce waste to date more than  mexican families have realized their dreams of home ownership  environmental recordedit cemex has been accused of violating environmental laws in the united states environmental watchdog groups and the united states environmental protection agency are threatening to file suit claiming the company has committed numerous violations of the clean air act in lyons colorado the united states environmental protection agency has also filed suit against cemex in victorville california claiming the company failed to install modern air pollution controls despite spending millions in renovations in the united kingdom cemex was originally fined £ on october  after hazardous dust was deposited up to three miles  km away from its rugby works the fine was the highest ever given under the integrated pollution prevention and control regulations and was also the highest for an environment agency prosecution for six years the fine was however judged excessive by the court of appeal and so reduced to £ in april  cemex announced that it had installed a £ million dust abatement system at the same works in rugby which had cut particulate emissions by  the site comes under the auspices of the eu waste incineration directive as it burns waste tyres for fuel there are concerns over the impact on both the environment and human health from this practice although it is common practice in many cement works during tests conducted from june  to august   the monterey bay california unified air pollution control district reported high levels of chromium vi also known as hexavalent chromium a cancer causing chemical agent at an elementary school and fire department in davenport california chromium vi is the contaminant that inspired the movie erin brockovich the toxic substance apparently originated from dust emitted by the cemex cement plant in davenport as the levels of chromium vi measured eight times the air districts acceptable level at pacific elementary school and  times at the davenport fire department both are located less than a halfmile from cemex chromium vi may have been unwittingly produced at the cemex plant in davenport for the last seven years according to ed kendig the executive director of the monterey bay unified air pollution control district its highly possible that chromium vi continues to be produced across the country as an accidental previously unknown byproduct of the cementmaking process in  the epa filed a complaint against cemex for violating federal air regulations at its victorville plant and in  cemex was cited for violations at plants in santa barbara and michigan  environmentalists and scientists are concerned for the monterey bay coastline where cemex has a sand mining operation in the city of marina ca the california coastal commission in march  issued a cease and desist order asking for administration civil penalties stating that the operation is narrowing beaches and impacting environmentally sensitive habitat cemex denies the allegations and as of may  continues to operate see alsoedit mexico portal companies portal main cemex competitors  global cement players are heidelbergcement votorantim cimentos unibeton ready mix list of companies traded on the bolsa mexicana de valores list of mexican companies economy of mexico referencesedit  sirkin harold l james w hemerling and arindam k bhattacharya  globality competing with everyone from everywhere for everything archived september   at the wayback machine new york business plus  isbn   a b corporate world headquarters  companys website archived february   at the wayback machine retrieved february    a b corporate headquarters according to companys website world locations map archived february   at the wayback machine retrieved february    a b corporate world headquarters at san pedro garza garcia  monterrey ml mexico per hoovers dun  bradstreet profile retrieved february    a b the headquarters remain in the bustling mexican industrial city of monterrey mexico  miles south of the texas border retrieved february    a b cemex corporate world headquarters situated in san pedro garza garcia mexico per linkedin retrieved february    httpswwwinfosyscomnewsroompressreleasespagesbusinesstransformationawardsaspx  reuters from  mexicos cemex to buy southdown of houston los angeles times issn  retrieved    cable mexico who are mexicos monopolists wikileaks  see also   source httpwwwfromthedojcomusdojblockscemexacquisitionofrinkerpermanent dead link  httpwwwjusticegovatrcasesfhtm  hugo chavez nationalizes cement industry cbs news april    factbox venezuelas nationalizations under hugo chavez reuters march     venezuela is set to take control of cemex plants the new york times august   retrieved april     cemex cemex and venezuela sign agreement on compensation for nationalization of cemex venezuela archived january   at the wayback machine  update mexicos cemex tumbles on peso derivatives reuters october     httpwwwfoolcominvestinginternat